  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And I will appoint over them four kinds, saith the Lord,.... Or four families (x), and these very devouring ones; that is, four sorts of punishment; and so the Targum, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"four evil punishments;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which are after mentioned. These are represented as under God, and at his beck and command; servants of his, that go and come at his pleasure, and do his will; and as being over men, and having power and authority to kill and to destroy by a divine commission: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the sword to slay: the first and chief of the four families or punishments, which had a commission from the Lord to sheath itself in his people, the Jews; even the sword of the enemy, the Chaldeans, drawn against them by a divine order and appointment: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the dogs to tear; the carcasses of those that are slain with the sword: or \"to draw\" (y); as the word signifies; it being the usual way of dogs to draw and drag the flesh about they are feeding on; this is another of the four families, and a very voracious one it is: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the fowls of the heaven, and the beasts of the earth, to devour and destroy; or \"to eat, and to corrupt\", the bodies of those that are slain by the sword. The meaning is, that such should not have a burial, but should be the food of fowls and wild beasts: these are the other two destroying families, which have their commission from the Lord for such service. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(x)  \"quatuor familias, sive cognationes\", Vatablus, Tigurine version, Calvin. (y) \"ad trahendum\", Calvin, Pagninus, Montanus, Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Schmidt; so Ben Melech, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(x)  \"quatuor familias, sive cognationes\", Vatablus, Tigurine version, Calvin. (y) \"ad trahendum\", Calvin, Pagninus, Montanus, Junius & Tremellius, Piscator, Schmidt; so Ben Melech, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
